name: Imposter Syndrome
description:
This is a personal game about my experience during Train Jam. This doesn't mean Train Jam is a bad thing. I actually think it is an amazing and the organizers do amazing job with it. I am glad that it is still happening. It is just me and how my brain works at that time period. 

I would like to apologize to all the people that I met, if my imposter weirdness caused any problems to them or made them feel any bad.

I am Sorry if I caused any problems or made anyone feel bad.

I hope this story could help other humans that may felt the same like me at some point in time. I used the train from the train jam logo to create the logo for the game so the affiliation for that goes to the designer behind it. Sorry if I am misusing it, feel free to let me know and I will change it.

.

.

.

P.S. You can use your mouse to highlight some of the text if it is difficult to read.

P.P.S. This game was partially developed during the same train jam because I felt it is sarcastic and reflect the theme of "UnExpected Anticipation".
